ichard d russo fortyfive pages richard d russos counter statement of proposed findings of fact and conclusions of law twentysix pages and richard d russos response to the division of enforcements proposed findings of fact and conclusions of law two pages all dated october   i issues the central issue is whether the undisclosed distribution of initial public offering ipo allocations by an investment adviser to certain investment company directors was illegal specifically did respondents willfully violate section a of the securities act and section b of the exchange act and rule b thereunder by not informing the monetta fund and the monetta trust the funds the funds shareholders and possible investors that the adviser allocated shares of hot ipos to the personal accounts of some funds directors and trustees did monetta financial services willfully violate section  and section  of the advisers act by not disclosing to the funds the funds shareholders and possible investors the allocation of hot ipos to certain directors and trustees and did mr bacarella cause and willfully aid and abet these violations by mfs did mr henry willfully violate section j of the investment company act and rule j thereunder by not including ipo transactions in a report required by rule j for the second quarter of  ii findings of facts my findings are based on the record and my observation of the witnesses demeanor i applied preponderance of the evidence as the applicable standard of proof see steadman v sec  us   i have considered all proposed findings and conclusions and arguments raised by the parties and accept those consistent with this decision in this decision the period february   through september   is the relevant period oip at  the commissions ability to punish persons for illegal activities is limited to actions that occurred up to five years before the commission initiated a proceeding see johnson v sec  fd  dc cir  since the commission initiated this proceeding on february   the actions subject to a penalty must have occurred on or after february   tr  div br at  resp br at  n div reply at  robert s bacarella mr bacarella graduated from st josephs college in  with a double major in accounting and finance he earned an mba from roosevelt university tr  mr bacarella was employed by the borgwarner corp borgwarner from  to  div ex  at b as a director of borgwarners pension investment department mr bacarella managed one mutual fund which began with assets of  million and peaked with assets of approximately  million tr  in june  mr bacarella formed monetta financial services inc mfs a delaware corporation and a registered investment adviser based in wheaton illinois and in may  he formed the monetta fund inc monetta fund a maryland corporation and an openend diversified investment company offering a single class of capital stock mfs and bacarella answer at  the monetta fund specializes in smallcap stocks and trades mainly overthecounter securities tr   the monetta funds assets increased dramatically in the early s from about  million to about  million on december   to  million at the end of  tr  div ex  at  div ex  at  in the  period the monetta fund gained between  million to  million of new assets each day tr  in january  mr bacarella created the monetta trust a massachusetts business trust and an openend diversified investment company the monetta trust offered three series of stock in  the midcap equity fund midcap fund the intermediate bond fund bond fund and the government money market fund mfs and bacarella answer at  resp ex a mfs has always been the investment adviser to the funds tr  jt stip  at  as was customary in the industry the monetta fund and the monetta trust had no employees in  tr  three funds were eligible to receive ipos  the monetta fund the midcap fund and the bond fund the monetta fund was by far the largest the midcap fund and the bond fund began doing business in march  after the relevant period began jt stip  at  in  the